Appendices: Complete Mathematical Derivations and Specifications

Appendix A: Proof of Theorem 5.1 - Mesh Collapse Theorem

A.1 Graph Model Definitions

Let G = (V, E) be an undirected graph representing a constellation of N nodes, where:

Â· V = {vâ‚, vâ‚‚, ..., v_N} are the compute nodes
Â· E = {(váµ¢, vâ±¼) | â€–ráµ¢ - râ±¼â€– â‰¤ d_max} are inter-satellite links

We assume nodes are uniformly distributed on a sphere of radius R (R = R_Earth + h).

A.2 Distance Distribution Derivation

The surface area of the sphere: A_s = 4Ï€RÂ²
