```

A.3 Relay Load Analysis

Consider a store-and-forward routing protocol. Each node must relay traffic for other nodes. The average path length (in hops) for a random pair of nodes scales as:

```
L_path âˆ âˆšN for 2D mesh
L_path âˆ N^(1/3) for 3D constellation
```

For a 3D constellation, the number of hops between two randomly chosen nodes is proportional to N^(1/3).

Each node serves as a relay for approximately (N-1) flows. The relay load per node:

```
L_relay(N) = (1/N) Î£_{iâ‰ j} [fraction of path(i,j) passing through node]
           âˆ (N-1)Â·L_path/N
           âˆ N^(1/3)
```

A.4 Energy-Per-Bit Scaling

Transmission energy per bit over distance d:

```
