Appendix D: Graph-Theoretic Analysis of Walker Constellations

D.1 Walker Delta Pattern Definition

A Walker Delta constellation is defined by parameters (T/P/F):

Â· T: Total number of satellites
Â· P: Number of orbital planes
Â· F: Relative spacing between satellites in adjacent planes
Â· h: Orbit altitude
Â· i: Inclination

Satellites are arranged with:

Â· S = T/P satellites per plane
Â· Î”Î© = 360Â°/P (right ascension difference between planes)
Â· Î”Î½ = 360Â°/S (mean anomaly difference within plane)
Â· Phase difference between planes: FÂ·(360Â°/T)

D.2 Graph Connectivity

For Walker constellation, each satellite has neighbors:

1. In-plane neighbors: 2 (forward and backward in same plane)
2. Cross-plane neighbors: Potentially 2 from adjacent planes

Total degree: k = 2 + 2Â·I(â€–Î”Î©Â·cos iâ€– â‰¤ d_max/R)

D.3 Path Length Analysis

The graph diameter (maximum hops between any two nodes):

```
D(G) = âŒˆ(P-1) + (S-1)âŒ‰ = P + S - 2
```

For optimal T = PÂ·S, minimizing diameter subject to fixed T:

```
Minimize: P + T/P - 2
Derivative: 1 - T/PÂ² = 0 â‡’ P = âˆšT
```

Thus optimal: P = âˆšT, S = âˆšT, giving D(G) = 2âˆšT - 2

D.4 Average Path Length

For random node pair (i,j):

```
E[hops] = (1/TÂ²) Î£_{pâ‚=0}^{P-1} Î£_{sâ‚=0}^{S-1} Î£_{pâ‚‚=0}^{P-1} Î£_{sâ‚‚=0}^{S-1} h((pâ‚,sâ‚),(pâ‚‚,sâ‚‚))
```

where h is hop count.

Approximation:

```
E[hops] â‰ˆ (P/3) + (S/3) for large P,S
```

D.5 Coordination Efficiency for Walker Pattern

Message complexity for global consensus:

```
Messages per node per round = kÂ·(broadcast to neighbors)
Total messages per sync = TÂ·kÂ·E[hops]
```

Substituting k â‰ˆ 4, E[hops] â‰ˆ (âˆšT)/3:

```
Total messages âˆ T^(3/2)
```

Thus coordination overhead per node:

```
C_overhead âˆ T^(1/2)
```

Compare to 3D mesh: C_overhead âˆ N^(1/3)

For T > 64, Walker has higher overhead than 3D mesh.

D.6 Optimal Walker Parameters

Given N nodes, find P,S,F to maximize connectivity while minimizing path length.

Optimization:

```
min_{P,S,F} Î±Â·D(G) + Î²Â·(1/connectivity)
subject to: PÂ·S = N, P,S âˆˆ â„¤âº, F âˆˆ {0,...,P-1}
```

Solution approximates:

```
P â‰ˆ S â‰ˆ âˆšN
F â‰ˆ P/2 (for even distribution)
```

D.7 Intersatellite Link Analysis

For satellite at (p,s) in plane p, satellite s:
Position vector:

```
r(t) = RÂ·[cos(Ï‰t + Î½â‚€ + sÎ”Î½)Â·(cos(Î©â‚€ + pÎ”Î©)cos(Ï‰t) - cos i sin(Î©â‚€ + pÎ”Î©)sin(Ï‰t)),
          sin(Ï‰t + Î½â‚€ + sÎ”Î½)Â·(sin(Î©â‚€ + pÎ”Î©)cos(Ï‰t) + cos i cos(Î©â‚€ + pÎ”Î©)sin(Ï‰t)),
