F.2.2 Slot Allocation Algorithm

```
Algorithm: Dynamic TDMA Allocation
Input: Queue lengths Q[i], node priorities P[i]
Output: Slot allocation A[i]

1: for each node i do
2:   Required slots R[i] = ceil(Q[i]/S_max)  // S_max = max data per slot
3:   Weight W[i] = P[i] * min(1, Q[i]/Q_max)
4: end for
5: 
6: Total required = Î£ R[i]
7: if Total required â‰¤ Available slots then
8:   // Proportional allocation
9:   A[i] = floor(Available slots * W[i]/Î£ W[j])
10: else
11:   // Weighted reduction
12:   Reduction factor Î± = Available slots / Total required
13:   A[i] = floor(Î± * R[i] * W[i])
14: end if
```

