F.3.2 Distance-Vector Algorithm

```
Algorithm: Modified Bellman-Ford for Orbital Networks
Input: Graph G, source s, parameters Î±,Î²,Î³
Output: Distance D[v], NextHop[v] for all v

1: Initialize D[s] = 0, D[v] = âˆ for v â‰  s
2: Initialize NextHop[v] = null
3: 
4: for i = 1 to |V|-1 do
5:   for each edge (u,v) in E do
6:     if D[u] + w(u,v) < D[v] then
7:       D[v] = D[u] + w(u,v)
8:       NextHop[v] = u
9:     end if
10:   end for
11: end for
```

